                             ‚ĖĄ  ‚Ėą
                              ‚ĖÄ‚ĖÄ


An automatic differentiation engine written in lean 4, a functional language with a
built-in proof checker, which also implements karpathy's microGPT both as a demo use
case and to parity-check its gradients against weights from the reference python
implementation.

It computes gradients the way pytorch does, but without mutating any state.

This lets it carry formal proofs that each operation is correct.

To show it works, it trains microGPT from scratch.

The result matches the python reference to eleven decimal places.

Run it with `lake exe parity`.
